OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FNo more easy deals for     
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25FRussian convicts freed to  
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5Ffight                      
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, Russia has been releasing prisoners to 
OL,6, fight in Ukraine for more than a year, 
OL,7, originally offering them a pardon and  
OL,8, freedom after six months, even if they 
OL,9, have been convicted of a violent crime.
OL,11,FBut the BBC has discovered this deal is
OL,12,Fa thing of the past. Now, they no      
OL,13,Flonger get a pardon, face tougher      
OL,14,Fconditions and instead of going home   
OL,15,Fearly, they must fight until the end of
OL,16,Fthe war.                               
OL,18,F"If you sign up now, be ready to die," 
OL,19,Fwrites a man called Sergei in a        
OL,20,Fchatroom for former Russian prisoners  
OL,21,Ffighting in Ukraine.                   
